From: Gal Pressman <gal@nvidia.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Sep 2024 14:28:02 +0300
Subject: octeontx2-pf: Remove setting of RX software timestamp
Patch-mainline: v6.12-rc1
Git-commit: eb87a1daf6fb3b1ba8f19d94e243a638a844a7cc
References: jsc#PED-11318

The responsibility for reporting of RX software timestamp has moved to
the core layer (see __ethtool_get_ts_info()), remove usage from the
device drivers.

Reviewed-by: Carolina Jubran <cjubran@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Rahul Rameshbabu <rrameshbabu@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Gal Pressman <gal@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Subbaraya Sundeep <sbhatta@marvell.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20240901112803.212753-15-gal@nvidia.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/octeontx2/nic/otx2_ethtool.c |    2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/octeontx2/nic/otx2_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/marvell/octeontx2/nic/otx2_ethtool.c
@@ -962,8 +962,6 @@ static int otx2_get_ts_info(struct net_d
 		return ethtool_op_get_ts_info(netdev, info);
 
 	info->so_timestamping = SOF_TIMESTAMPING_TX_SOFTWARE |
-				SOF_TIMESTAMPING_RX_SOFTWARE |
-				SOF_TIMESTAMPING_SOFTWARE |
 				SOF_TIMESTAMPING_TX_HARDWARE |
 				SOF_TIMESTAMPING_RX_HARDWARE |
 				SOF_TIMESTAMPING_RAW_HARDWARE;
